### MikroTik OSPF & Network Troubleshooting Cheat Sheet
### Basic Connectivity

/ping <Cisco-OSPF-IP> interface=vmbr2 count=20       # basic reachability
/interface bridge host print where bridge=vmbr2     # learned MACs
/ip arp print where interface~"vmbr|ether|vlan"    # ARP table check

OSPF Neighbor & Adjacency

/routing ospf neighbor print detail                     # neighbor state, DR/BDR, timers, uptime
/routing ospf neighbor print detail where state!=full   # non-full neighbors only
/routing ospf interface-template print detail           # v7 templates â€“ hello/dead, auth, MTU, network-type
/routing ospf interface print detail                    # per-interface status
/routing ospf instance print detail                     # instances, router-id, redistribution
/routing ospf area print                                # configured areas

OSPF Routes & Database

/routing ospf route print                               # OSPF routes in table
/ip route print where active and gateway-status~"O"    # full table with OSPF entries
/routing ospf lsa print                                 # LSDB overview
/routing ospf lsa print detail where type=router        # Type-1 LSAs

Logging & Real-Time Debug

/system logging add topics=ospf,route,!raw action=memory disabled=no
/log print follow where topics~"ospf|route"           # live logs (MTU/auth/hello errors)
/system logging remove [find topics~"ospf"]          # disable logging

Quick Resets

/routing ospf instance reset [find]                    # restart OSPF process
/routing ospf instance disable [find]; /routing ospf instance enable [find]  # full restart

Firewall / Protocol Allow

/ip firewall filter add chain=input action=accept protocol=ospf place-before=0 comment="Allow OSPF (protocol 89)"



